                            <comment id="17388116" author="rhauch" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 14:50:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify what appears to have happened.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kpatelatwork&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kpatelatwork&quot;&gt;kpatelatwork&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/11132&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;mentions in a comment on the PR&lt;/a&gt;, the behavior of the Connect restart API in AK 2.8 and earlier was always to return &quot;204 NO CONTENT&quot;, not &quot;200 OK&quot; as mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-745%3A+Connect+API+to+restart+connector+and+tasks&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;KIP-745&lt;/a&gt;. Although the code used `Response.ok().build()`, the `RestClient` always processed the absence of a response body as `204 NO CONTENT`. So, to maintain the actual AK 2.x behavior in this branch of the code, we should instead return `204 NO CONTENT`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve corrected the KIP to reflect this older actual behavior of returning &quot;204 NO CONTENT&quot;. It was a minor but necessary correction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that we have &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; changed the KIP or the behavior of returning &quot;202 ACCEPTED&quot; when `includeTasks=true` and/or `failedOnly=true`. These cases correspond to the new behavior added in KIP-745.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17388332" author="kpatelatwork" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 22:33:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rhauch&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rhauch&quot;&gt;rhauch&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kkonstantine&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kkonstantine&quot;&gt;kkonstantine&lt;/a&gt; for taking care of the fix and unblocking the release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
